Ruben Tous in an expert in data engineering and machine learning. He got his Ph.D in
Computer Science and Digital Communication from UPF (Universitat Pompeu Fabra,
Barcelona, Spain) in 2006. Currently he is an associate professor in the Department
of Computer Architechture of the Universitat Politècnica de Catalunya (UPC) and researcher of the CROMAI group (Computational Resources Orchestration and Management for AI). From 2022 he leads BIMAI, the Barcelona Image and Artificial Intelligence Lab. Previously he was scientific advisor at Adsmurai, associate researcher at the Barcelona Supercomputing Center (BSC), lecturer and researcher at the Universitat Pompeu Fabra (UPF) and programmer at Cap Gemini Ernst&Young. He has published two books and more than 70 research papers. He is co-editor of several MPEG and JPEG standards and has been Co-Chairman of the JPEG's Metadata Group. He
has been involved in 15 competitive funded research projects, including two European
Networks of Excellence and one European Integrated Project. He's currenly involved in the project UPC-Computación de Altas Prestaciones VIII (PID2019-107255GB-C22) led by funded with 436,689 byt

